{{ NCAATeamSeason | Mode = football | Year = 2011 | Team = South Carolina Gamecocks | Image= South Carolina Gamecocks football wordmark.svg | ImageSize= 150px | Conference= Southeastern Conference | Division= Eastern | ShortConference= SEC | CoachRank = 9 | APRank = 10 | BCSRank = 9 | Record = 10â2 | ConfRecord = 6â2 | HeadCoach = [[Steve Spurrier]] | HCYear = 7th | OffCoach= | DefCoach= Ellis Johnson | OScheme= Multiple | DScheme= 4-2-5 | StadiumArena= [[Williams-Brice Stadium]] | Champion = | BowlTourney = [[2012 Capital One Bowl|Capital One Bowl]] vs. [[2011 Nebraska Cornhuskers football team|Nebraska]] | BowlTourneyResult = }} {{2011 SEC football standings}} The '''2011 South Carolina Gamecocks football team''' represents the [[University of South Carolina]] in the [[2011 NCAA Division I FBS football season]]. The Gamecocks are led by seventh-year head coach [[Steve Spurrier]] and play their home games at [[Williams-Brice Stadium]]. They are a member of the Eastern Division of the [[Southeastern Conference]].
==Preseason== On April 10, 2011, the Garnet squad defeated the Black squad, 21â17, in the annual Garnet & Black Spring Game, in front of a crowd of 30,100.
